#: ../../../guides/recipes/add-binary-cache.md:2
msgid "Configure Nix to use a custom binary cache"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/add-binary-cache.md:4
msgid ""
"Nix can be configured to use a binary cache with the [`substituters`]"
"(https://nix.dev/manual/nix/2.21/command-ref/conf-file.html#conf-"
"substituters) and [`trusted-public-keys`](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/2.21/"
"command-ref/conf-file.html#conf-trusted-public-keys) settings, either "
"exclusively or in addition to cache.nixos.org."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/add-binary-cache.md:7
msgid ""
"Follow the tutorial to [set up an HTTP binary cache](setup-http-binary-"
"cache) and create a key pair for signing store objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/add-binary-cache.md:10
msgid ""
"For example, given a binary cache at `https://example.org` with public key "
"`My56...Q==%`, and some derivation in `default.nix`, make Nix exclusively "
"use that cache once by passing [settings as command line flags](https://nix."
"dev/manual/nix/2.21/command-ref/conf-file#command-line-flags):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/add-binary-cache.md:12
msgid ""
"$ nix-build --substituters https://example.org --trusted-public-keys example."
"org:My56...Q==%\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/add-binary-cache.md:16
msgid ""
"To permanently use the custom cache in addition to the public cache, add to "
"the [Nix configuration file](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/2.21/command-ref/"
"conf-file#configuration-file):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/add-binary-cache.md:18
msgid ""
"$ echo \"extra-substituters = https://example.org\" >> /etc/nix/nix.conf\n"
"$ echo \"extra-trusted-public-keys = example.org:My56...Q==%\" >> /etc/nix/"
"nix.conf\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/add-binary-cache.md:23
msgid "To always use only the custom cache:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/add-binary-cache.md:25
msgid ""
"$ echo \"substituters = https://example.org\" >> /etc/nix/nix.conf\n"
"$ echo \"trusted-public-keys = example.org:My56...Q==%\" >> /etc/nix/nix."
"conf\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/add-binary-cache.md:30
msgid "NixOS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/add-binary-cache.md:31
msgid ""
"On NixOS, Nix is configured through the [`nix.settings`](https://search."
"nixos.org/options?show=nix.settings) option:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/recipes/add-binary-cache.md:33
msgid ""
"{ ... }: {\n"
"  nix.settings = {\n"
"    substituters = [ \"https://example.org\" ];\n"
"    trusted-public-keys = [ \"example.org:My56...Q==%\" ];\n"
"  };\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
